org.icefaces.ace.component.progressbar

Class ProgressBarBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.faces.component.UIComponent
      • javax.faces.component.UIComponentBase
        • org.icefaces.ace.component.progressbar.ProgressBarBase
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.EventListener, javax.faces.component.behavior.ClientBehaviorHolder, javax.faces.component.PartialStateHolder, javax.faces.component.StateHolder, javax.faces.component.TransientStateHolder, javax.faces.event.ComponentSystemEventListener, javax.faces.event.FacesListener, javax.faces.event.SystemEventListenerHolder, IceClientBehaviorHolder, IProgressBar
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ProgressBar

    public abstract class ProgressBarBase
extends javax.faces.component.UIComponentBase
implements IProgressBar, IceClientBehaviorHolder
    The Progress Bar is a process status indicator that can either work purely on client side or interact with server side using ajax.

    For more information, see the ProgressBar Wiki Documentation.
